      "writtenOn": "2021-06-11T21:03:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We do have a special accessor for sk_FragColor; this code handles declarations, not accesses.\n\nI agree that the magic leaking out of IRGenerator is not ideal. Long term, we can certainly come up with a better solution - maybe have IRGenerator return a nop or something in this case so it\u0027s at least returning something, or potentially even just kill the ability to redeclare sk_FragColor altogether (Do we really need to support that? Maybe, I don\u0027t know). \n\nBut wherever the special handling for this variable lives, I think it needs to be no farther out than here; I don\u0027t want DSLParser having to do anything special, since DSLParser represents something that end users should (eventually) be able to write using public APIs.\n\nIn the short term I think probably the best way to address this is just to verify that the variable we failed to declare was in fact sk_FragColor before we grab it from the symbol table, which should at least guarantee no weird side effects. Sound good?",
